v class=\"pencraft pc-display-flex pc-gap-8 pc-reset\"><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container restack-image\"><svg role=\"img\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 20 20\" fill=\"none\" stroke-width=\"1.5\" stroke=\"var(--color-fg-primary)\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\"><g><title></title><path d=\"M2.53001 7.81595C3.49179 4.73911 6.43281 2.5 9.91173 2.5C13.1684 2.5 15.9537 4.46214 17.0852 7.23684L17.6179 8.67647M17.6179 8.67647L18.5002 4.26471M17.6179 8.67647L13.6473 6.91176M17.4995 12.1841C16.5378 15.2609 13.5967 17.5 10.1178 17.5C6.86118 17.5 4.07589 15.5379 2.94432 12.7632L2.41165 11.3235M2.41165 11.3235L1.5293 15.7353M2.41165 11.3235L6.38224 13.0882\"></path></g></svg></button><button tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\" class=\"pencraft pc-reset pencraft icon-container view-image\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"20\" height=\"20\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-maximize2 lucide-maximize-2\"><polyline points=\"15 3 21 3 21 9\"></polyline><polyline points=\"9 21 3 21 3 15\"></polyline><line x1=\"21\" x2=\"14\" y1=\"3\" y2=\"10\"></line><line x1=\"3\" x2=\"10\" y1=\"21\" y2=\"14\"></line></svg></button></div></div></div></a></figure></div><p>One of the great confusions of the modern world—now magnified by artificial intelligence—is the belief that our deepest human problem is biological, neurological, or informational.</p><p>It is not.</p><p>Scripture, tradition, and lived experience all testify to a harder truth: <strong>the fundamental</strong> <strong>human problem is spiritual</strong>. And spiritual problems are not merely healed. <strong>They require salvation.</strong></p><p>As <strong>Bishop Robert Barron</strong> often explains, <em>sin is not a wound from which we simply recover; it is a condition from which we must be saved</em>. Healing implies restoration within the system. Salvation requires intervention from beyond it.</p><p>This distinction matters profoundly in an age of AI.</p><p>Artificial intelligence can model behavior, optimize outcomes, predict patterns, and generate insight. But <strong>AI cannot sin—and therefore cannot understand sin from the inside.</strong> It has no conscience, no culpability, no rupture with God. It knows nothing of guilt, repentance, grace, or mercy except as data.</p><p>And this is where many modern psychol…</p>"}